From 3bf612f89c0490442aa860c0660c05cb58b6d163 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: =?UTF-8?q?Petr=20=C5=A0tetiar?= <petr.stetiar@prplfoundation.org>
Date: Tue, 26 Mar 2024 16:10:14 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] WIP: amxb_usp_common: workaround poll timeout by increasing
 it to 3 seconds
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

strace we took on boot showed that the handshake does complete, but
after the 2 seconds deadline. As shared during prplOs increasing the
timeout here won't be a long term solution as, while waiting on that
poll, tr181-device won't proxy anymore  other request on regulare ubus
on Device. which is very central in the overall system.  Redoing the
handshake itself would fail due to duplicate endpoint error sent by
obuspa.  So the handshake/register flow will need to be reworked to
account for bigger delay without blocking  and allow retry of the
register part.

As it will likely take  a couple of weeks to rework the call flow and
properly test it, we might just temporarily increase the poll timeout to
3 or 4 seconds for immediate purpose of unlocking the tests.

So lets start with the 3s timeout.

Suggested-by: Vincent Harle <vincent.harle@softathome.com>
Signed-off-by: Petr Štetiar <petr.stetiar@prplfoundation.org>
---
 src/amxb_usp_common.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/amxb_usp_common.c b/src/amxb_usp_common.c
index c55a3a712fcb..8ae5fedf4b13 100644
--- a/src/amxb_usp_common.c
+++ b/src/amxb_usp_common.c
@@ -158,7 +158,7 @@ static int amxb_usp_wait_for_handshake(amxb_usp_t* amxb_usp_ctx) {
     fds[0].fd = amxb_usp_get_fd(amxb_usp_ctx);
     fds[0].events = POLLIN;
 
-    retval = poll(fds, 1, 2 * 1000);
+    retval = poll(fds, 1, 2 * 1500);
     if(retval <= 0) {
         retval = -1;
         goto exit;
